 Below is the graph of some function $f(x)$. $AB \parallel x-$ axis
 And $f(x)$ is a strictly increasing function
%
\begin{align}

\includegraphics[scale=1.5]{figure.svg}
\end{align}
%text
%

reason.tex:
%text
 $AB \parallel x-$axis $\implies \dydx = 0$ between $A$ and $B$. Hence, while $f(x)$ is an increasing function, it is \underline\text{not strictly increasing}
 A function is strictly increasing (in some domain) if $\dydx > 0$ but not $\geq 0$%
